in vanilla JavaScript. This also provides an excellent package build size to maximise performance.</p> <h2 id="module-bundlers"><a href="#module-bundlers" aria-hidden="true" class="header-anchor">#</a> Module Bundlers</h2> <p>If you are using a module bundler such as <a href="https://webpack.js.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Webpack<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 100 100" width="15" height="15" class="icon outbound"><path fill="currentColor" d="M18.8,85.1h56l0,0c2.2,0,4-1.8,4-4v-32h-8v28h-48v-48h28v-8h-32l0,0c-2.2,0-4,1.8-4,4v56C14.8,83.3,16.6,85.1,18.8,85.1z"></path> <polygon fill="currentColor" points="45.7,48.7 51.3,54.3 77.2,28.5 77.2,37.2 85.2,37.2 85.2,14.9 62.8,14.9 62.8,22.9 71.5,22.9"></polygon></svg></a> (recommended), then you will still be easily able to import flexCarousel.js as you need.</p></div> <div class="meta"><p>
